  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening WASH service delivery for refugees and host communities in Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As the protracted political and consequent humanitarian crises in Uganda&apos;s neighbouring countries of South Sudan and the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) continue, increased coordinated and effective humanitarian assistance is required to meet the basic needs of refugees already hosted by Uganda, as well as of those arriving on a daily basis. Through his project, IOM proposes sustainable and cost-effective WASH interventions at the two hosting settlements of Kyangwali and Kyaka II, as well as improved sanitation coverage at Palorinya.</narrative>
  </description>
